-All right, all right...
-Runner! Stop!

01:35.733 --> 01:38.600
-2 Adam 15...
-2 Adam 15, foot pursuit.

01:41.067 --> 01:43.767
-Foot pursuit, eastbound.
-Eastbound Battlefield, he's...

01:43.800 --> 01:46.900
-Campbell, and...
the-- the Walgreen's.

01:46.933 --> 01:49.700
-Stop, police!

01:49.733 --> 01:53.167
-(sirens)

01:55.433 --> 01:57.300
-White male, dark hair,
with a beard.

01:57.333 --> 01:59.433
It's a gray or blue t-shirt.

02:03.800 --> 02:06.100
-Hey, let's go down here
to where we last saw him.

02:06.133 --> 02:08.233
-Yeah. Shoulda had him.
-Crap!

02:08.267 --> 02:10.800
-(radio chatter)

02:10.833 --> 02:14.933
-All right, so...
we rounded here,
came this way...

02:14.967 --> 02:18.633
-We lost him right there
at those trees.

02:18.667 --> 02:23.367
-(radio chatter)

02:23.400 --> 02:25.767
-2 Adam 15.
There should be two occupants

02:25.800 --> 02:29.267
in a silver car right there
next to a car.

02:29.300 --> 02:31.733
Start lookin' under stuff.

02:35.067 --> 02:37.833
-He was last seen just north
of, at the apartments.

02:37.867 --> 02:39.800
So I don't know
if he's in these bushes
right here or not.

02:39.833 --> 02:42.733
Um, he just disappeared
when we got to the apartments.

02:44.167 --> 02:47.967
I mean, you were there.
-Last saw him...
40 feet away.

02:49.200 --> 02:51.300
-'Cause I was right--
I mean, you were--

02:51.333 --> 02:53.233
-He was west of,
and it looked like
he weaved in.

02:53.267 --> 02:54.700
And that's the last I saw.

02:54.733 --> 02:56.400
I coulda swore
he was in here somewhere.

02:56.433 --> 02:57.933
And he might be.

02:57.967 --> 03:00.933
-(exhaling)
He came right through here.
Last time we saw him

03:00.967 --> 03:03.400
was right there.

03:03.433 --> 03:06.700
Don't move! Put your hands up!
-Put your hands up!

03:06.733 --> 03:09.367
Hands up!
-Both of 'em!
Get that other one up!

03:09.400 --> 03:11.400
Step up!
Stand up!

03:11.433 --> 03:15.067
-Get on your belly!
Get on your belly now!

03:15.067 --> 03:16.367
Get on your belly now!

03:16.400 --> 03:17.600
-Apologize.

03:17.633 --> 03:19.133
-Get your hand
behind your back now!
Get it out!

03:20.667 --> 03:22.500
Get your hands behind your back!

03:22.533 --> 03:24.633
-My other hand's stuck.

03:24.667 --> 03:26.067
-Don't move!

03:26.067 --> 03:28.400
-Get on your feet.

03:28.433 --> 03:29.533
Get on your feet.

03:29.567 --> 03:31.667
-I need help.
-Roll over.

03:31.700 --> 03:33.300
Do you have any weapons on you?

03:33.333 --> 03:35.067
-We got one in custody...
-Huh?

03:35.067 --> 03:36.600
All right.
Can you sit up?
I'm gonna help you

03:36.633 --> 03:39.367
outta these bushes.
You ready?
one, two, three...(grunts)

03:39.400 --> 03:41.667
Hey, we need somebody
go contact the car
that he was in

03:41.700 --> 03:43.433
over there.
-I have a warrant.

03:43.467 --> 03:45.300
-I know you do.
That's why
we're chasin' you.

03:45.333 --> 03:46.800
That's why you ran, right?
-Yes, sir.

03:46.833 --> 03:48.467
-Not hurt or anything?
-No.

03:48.500 --> 03:49.967
-Pride hurt a little bit?
-Yeah.

03:50.067 --> 03:52.467
-Mine is, too, 'cause
you lost us for a second, but...
(chuckles)

03:52.500 --> 03:54.433
-All right. What's
your probation warrant for?

03:54.467 --> 03:57.133
-Just a violation.
-Just a violation?
What'd you violate?

03:57.167 --> 03:58.867
I don't wanna say right now.
-Okay.

03:58.900 --> 04:01.333
-He's sayin'
that he has
a probation violation.

04:01.367 --> 04:04.300
We were actually looking
for a male associated
with the vehicle

04:04.333 --> 04:07.300
who had a couple
of domestic violence
warrants, so...

04:07.333 --> 04:09.633
-All right. I'm gonna
have you sit in the car
a sec, okay?

04:09.667 --> 04:12.233
Just have a seat in there.
However you wanna get in,
I don't care.

04:12.267 --> 04:15.100
Okay, just be careful
not to hit your head.

04:15.133 --> 04:18.567
You can do it.
Wuh wuh, I'm gonna
help you there,

04:18.600 --> 04:21.533
just a little bit,
just-- you got it.

04:21.567 --> 04:23.100
There you go.

04:23.133 --> 04:26.667
I'm gonna go talk
to this girl over here
and see what's goin' on.

04:26.700 --> 04:29.633
-(radio chatter)

04:32.067 --> 04:34.467
Do you have a female?
-Yeah, she's in my car.

04:34.500 --> 04:36.467
-Okay. We're gonna
go talk to her.

04:37.533 --> 04:40.267
-This is unbelievable.
-It is unbelievable.

04:40.300 --> 04:42.133
Come out and talk to us,
let's see what's goin' on here.

04:42.167 --> 04:44.300
-I don't really
know him that well.
-Okay, well, hold on a second.

04:44.333 --> 04:47.200
What-- so, what is goin' on,
'cause I saw you guys--

04:47.233 --> 04:50.267
I saw him get outta your car
and walk across the parkin' lot,
and he--

04:50.300 --> 04:51.833
looked like
he picked somethin' up,
and he kinda

04:51.867 --> 04:53.633
went behind that, uh...
propane container.

04:53.667 --> 04:57.533
-I wasn't paying attention,
I was on the phone
with my friend, she knows him.

04:57.567 --> 04:59.333
-She knows him?
-I don't really know him
real well.

04:59.367 --> 05:02.300
He seems like the nicest--
real nice person...
-So why are you here?

05:02.333 --> 05:05.833
Why are you and that person
at this location?
-Oh, I've come here today

05:05.867 --> 05:09.767
to visit my friend,
and I was gonna return
his pots and pans...

05:09.800 --> 05:11.800
-Okay.
-and uh... yeah...

05:11.833 --> 05:14.867
-So, you brought him with you
just for... company or what?

05:14.900 --> 05:17.133
-Yeah, yeah, 'cause he didn't
have really nowhere to go.

05:17.167 --> 05:19.167
-Oh, okay, so you
were comin' up here to re--
-He's gonna live

05:19.200 --> 05:20.867
with my friend's mom
in Bolivar.
-Okay.

05:20.900 --> 05:23.267
-And she was on the phone
when this all happened,
and I could hear her going,

05:23.300 --> 05:27.200
Tina? He has a warrant,
and it's like, I was like,
you know, really? Really?

05:27.233 --> 05:29.833
-I understand.
So you came up here
to return some items

05:29.867 --> 05:31.733
you purchased?
-And just comin'
to visit some friends.

05:31.767 --> 05:33.467
-Okay. Why did he
go in the store
and you didn't?

05:33.500 --> 05:35.700
-I didn't wanna go in there.
I didn't have anything
to go there for.

05:35.733 --> 05:37.700
-Oh, you weren't returning
the items here.
-No, I wasn't even

05:37.733 --> 05:40.167
goin' in there.
I think-- no,
I was on the phone with her,

05:40.200 --> 05:42.400
I wasn't paying attention...
-Why did he tell you

05:42.433 --> 05:45.300
to stop here, then?
-He didn't, he was driving.

05:45.333 --> 05:47.667
-Oh, he was driving.
-I let him drive my new car,
yes, okay?

05:47.700 --> 05:50.400
-Oh, okay...
-Hey, Tina, is this
your new car over here?

05:50.433 --> 05:52.067
-Yes.
-Do you care if I search
the car, make sure

05:52.067 --> 05:54.133
there's nothing illegal
in there?
-No...

05:54.167 --> 05:56.333
-Great. Great.
-You're not gettin' arrested
or anything like that.

05:56.367 --> 05:58.800
-Great. Okay.

05:58.833 --> 06:02.200
We got consent from the owner
to conduct a search.

06:02.233 --> 06:06.100
Currently searching the vehicle
for any illegal contraband.

06:06.133 --> 06:10.067
Uh, we haven't found anything
that is illegal at this time.

06:10.067 --> 06:11.200
-(horn honks)

06:15.100 --> 06:16.500
-Had to get medical out here.

06:16.533 --> 06:19.900
He was running
pretty fast a minute ago.
Now he's claiming

06:19.933 --> 06:22.533
that he's taken
some methamphetamine.
He said he ingested

06:22.567 --> 06:24.367
some earlier, so I don't know

06:24.400 --> 06:27.867
if maybe from the--
from the run, gettin'
his heart rate up,

06:27.900 --> 06:29.667
that, uh, along
with the methamphetamine,

06:29.700 --> 06:31.933
it's caused him
to have some heart palpitations.

06:31.967 --> 06:34.700
But, uh, we'll
have to get him cleared
before we take him to jail

06:34.733 --> 06:36.700
and make sure he's okay.

06:36.733 --> 06:40.367
Ma'am? All right,
just back up here,
and then go out on this side

06:40.400 --> 06:43.067
of the parking lot.
You're free to leave,
all right?

06:43.067 --> 06:46.800
Uh, the medics are sayin'
that they're wanting to take him
to the hospital.

06:46.833 --> 06:51.067
He's profusely sweating.
-Yeah. He's told the officer
that he used methamphetamine

06:51.067 --> 06:54.667
earlier today, so we're
gonna have to, uh,
follow the ambulance

06:54.700 --> 06:57.733
to the hospital,
and we'll sit on him
until he gets medically cleared,

06:57.767 --> 06:59.200
and then we'll take him
to jail.

06:59.233 --> 07:02.067
End of the day,
he's still goin' to jail.

07:05.533 --> 07:08.333
-Um... I go to the gym
whenever I can

07:08.367 --> 07:11.300
to try to maintain
a certain standard.

07:11.333 --> 07:13.400
Whenever duck season
comes in season,

07:13.433 --> 07:15.067
I'll go duck huntin' as well.

07:15.067 --> 07:18.733
Kinda helps-- gets me away
from my, uh... my job,
and hang out

07:18.767 --> 07:20.500
with some friends
who aren't in law enforcement.

07:20.533 --> 07:23.933
Helps me unwind.

07:23.967 --> 07:29.600
Got behind this van--
it's showin' a pattern
of drivin' erratic.

07:29.633 --> 07:33.333
I'm gonna go talk to her
about not usin' a turn signal
back there.

07:35.500 --> 07:37.067
-Hey!
-Huh?

07:37.067 --> 07:39.567
-I'm Deputy Kophazy
of the Sheriff's Office.
How are you?

07:39.600 --> 07:43.233
-I'm okay.
-Okay. Why didn't you--
why didn't you use your--

07:43.267 --> 07:47.667
um, turn signal in here?
-Because somebody
was aggravatin' the crap

07:47.700 --> 07:50.300
outta me on the phone.
-Oh, okay.

07:50.333 --> 07:52.967
-Um, that's all.
-You got your driver's license
with you?

07:53.067 --> 07:57.067
-Yeah. See?
-Let me see your
driver's license, dear.

07:57.100 --> 07:59.233
-Yeah, I'm gettin' it.
-(radio chatter)

07:59.267 --> 08:03.300
-It's gonna be a white van.
Stand by for the tag.

08:05.067 --> 08:10.067
-If you got a
heat car,
can you send 'em this way?)

08:10.100 --> 08:11.900
-(radio chatter)

08:11.933 --> 08:15.400
-My stepmom used to work
for Richmond County,
her name's Sherry.

08:15.433 --> 08:19.067
-I'm sorry, I was listenin'
to my radio, what--
what'd you say?

08:19.067 --> 08:21.233
-My stepmother,
she used to be, um...
I don't know

08:21.267 --> 08:23.467
if she still is on the force,
but... Sherry?

08:23.500 --> 08:26.467
-Sherry. Okay.
Are you staying here tonight?

08:26.500 --> 08:30.733
-No, actually... like I said,
somebody was aggravating
the crap outta me,

08:30.767 --> 08:34.533
and um... somebody
is in room 322.
They just want me

08:34.567 --> 08:36.100
to give 'em a ride

08:36.133 --> 08:37.967
to the liquor store.
I don't even know where
that's at...

08:38.067 --> 08:39.567
-322?
-Yeah.

08:39.600 --> 08:41.700
-Well, this is 410 and 409.
-I know, I don't know
where it's at,

08:41.733 --> 08:43.600
so I parked right here
and I was about to walk...

08:43.633 --> 08:46.167
-Okay.
-but I couldn't use the phone
'cause... my boyfriend

08:46.200 --> 08:48.067
was blowin'-- blowin' me up.

08:48.100 --> 08:49.967
-Is anybody else in this car?
-No.

08:50.067 --> 08:53.067
-It's a pretty big nice van.
-This is your car, right?

08:53.067 --> 08:56.233
-Yeah.
-Okay. Come on over here,
for me.

08:56.267 --> 08:58.967
You can hang out with me.
Okay, is there anything
in that car

08:59.067 --> 09:01.133
you ain't supposed to have
that's gonna get you
in trouble?

09:01.167 --> 09:03.967
-No.
-No? Are you under the influence
of anything right now?

09:04.067 --> 09:07.700
-I been cryin'.
-You been cryin'?
What's you been cryin' for?

09:07.733 --> 09:11.667
-Life's stressful situations.
-I think everybody's
got those, right?

09:11.700 --> 09:13.900
-Yeah.
-Would you have any problem
with me takin' a look

09:13.933 --> 09:16.267
in your vehicle, make sure
you don't have any narcotics
in there?

09:16.300 --> 09:19.300
-No. Look.
-I can? Okay.

09:19.333 --> 09:22.333
And nothin' on you
you ain't supposed to have,
nothin' hidden...

09:22.367 --> 09:23.833
-No.
-on you?

09:23.867 --> 09:27.067
-Nothin' hidden
on me, no, nothin'.
-Nothin' in your wallet?

09:27.067 --> 09:31.100
In your little wallet thing?
-Uh-uh.

09:31.133 --> 09:33.567
-Can you open up
that little zipper for me?

09:34.867 --> 09:37.333
-What's that?
-This is
a blood pressure pill.

09:37.367 --> 09:41.333
-Let me see what you got there.
-It's a hydrochloride...

09:41.367 --> 09:43.700
-Okay.
-For high blood pressure.

09:43.733 --> 09:46.500
-Okay. Do your arms
like this.

09:48.700 --> 09:50.667
-I'm not a druggie.
I don't shoot no needles
or nothin'.

09:50.700 --> 09:52.400
-Okay.
You just actin'
a little funny.

09:52.433 --> 09:55.133
Tell you what, will you
go hang out with Deputy Jones
back here?

09:55.167 --> 09:56.767
-'Cause y'all are scary...
-We're scary?

09:56.800 --> 10:00.100
-I was irritated (bleep).
You have no idea, like...
-What is there about me

10:00.133 --> 10:04.733
that makes you intimidated?
-Not you (indistinct).

10:04.767 --> 10:08.000
-(radio chatter)
-(indistinct) "Are you
with my boyfriend?"

10:08.033 --> 10:13.600
And that's why I turned around
right there and um...
they keep-- whoever, uh...

10:13.633 --> 10:15.800
-You don't know
who you're supposed
to pick up at the hotel?

10:15.833 --> 10:18.100
-I forget-- I forgot his name.

10:18.133 --> 10:21.033
Because he's a friend of mine's
friend, and he's the one
wants a ride to the liquor store

10:21.067 --> 10:24.033
before they close.
I told him there's one open
on (indistinct) Road,

10:24.067 --> 10:27.233
-'cause (indistinct) her life.
-Yeah, yeah. Hang tight here
with Deputy Jones, okay?

10:27.267 --> 10:31.000
-(radio chatter)
-We stopped a female
for a traffic violation.

10:31.033 --> 10:33.467
She didn't use a turn signal
when she pulled into here.

10:33.500 --> 10:36.000
When she got out,
she appears to be
under the influence

10:36.033 --> 10:40.000
of some kind of substance,
so we're gonna make sure
there's no kinda narcotic

10:40.033 --> 10:41.700
in her vehicle.

10:41.733 --> 10:45.200
It's a pill that's
not in a prescription bottle.

10:47.367 --> 10:51.333
There's a whole lot
more pills that are not
in an approved bottle.

10:53.067 --> 10:57.600
Deputy Justice is performing
the evaluations to see
if she was okay to drive,

10:57.633 --> 11:00.167
and as soon
as he finishes that,
we're gonna go talk to her.

11:00.200 --> 11:05.367
-So while searching,
Deputy Jones located
a folded up dollar bill,

11:05.400 --> 11:09.900
in a particular way
that's consistent
with narcotics,

11:09.933 --> 11:14.733
and inside
it appears there's gonna be...
looks like cocaine.

11:14.767 --> 11:17.300
We'll test it
and figure out
what it is.

11:17.333 --> 11:18.800
That was found up top, Ryan?

11:18.833 --> 11:21.200
-Yeah, right up here,
tucked to the right.
-I seen her reachin'

11:21.233 --> 11:22.867
before she got out.
-Okay.

11:22.900 --> 11:25.133
So it's probably consistent
with what she was doin'.

11:25.167 --> 11:26.333
Let me go talk to her
real quick.

11:26.367 --> 11:28.200
Apparently while Justice
was doing SFST,

11:28.233 --> 11:30.067
she was about to fall asleep.

11:30.100 --> 11:33.767
-Earlier?
-You're under the influence
of a CNS depressant.

11:33.800 --> 11:37.267
-No, you can't
read me anything.
-Well, I have to...

11:37.300 --> 11:39.467
-I'm not
under the influence of...

11:39.500 --> 11:41.333
-Okay, but I have
to read you this, okay?

11:41.367 --> 11:43.333
-All right, ma'am...
-No, I have not
had a drink yet.

11:43.367 --> 11:44.967
-Have a seat, ma'am.
No, you ain't been drinkin',

11:45.067 --> 11:47.600
but you been takin'...
-I have not been takin'...

11:47.633 --> 11:51.667
anything, I haven't slept
in like three days.

11:51.700 --> 11:54.200
-Look here, you said
I could search
your vehicle, correct?

11:54.233 --> 11:56.367
Do you wanna talk
about some of the stuff
I found in your vehicle?

11:56.400 --> 11:59.500
-Well, no, first of all,
because, no, I don't recall
sayin' I gave you a right

11:59.533 --> 12:02.767
to search my whole vehicle.
You said is there anything
in there that I might

12:02.800 --> 12:06.367
know about, or...
-No, that's correct,
I did ask you that.

12:06.400 --> 12:10.567
You said, yes I can search.
-No, not search
the whole thing...

12:10.600 --> 12:13.467
-Okay, so when I asked
if I could search,
you meant if I can search

12:13.500 --> 12:16.500
like one portion of it,
that what the understanding
you were in, or...

12:16.533 --> 12:21.767
-Yeah, like, look in there
and there's no... alcohol.
-Okay. Okay.

12:21.800 --> 12:25.100
-First off, do you wanna
talk about what I found
in the vehicle?

12:25.133 --> 12:26.933
That's a yes or a no, ma'am.

12:26.967 --> 12:30.767
Okay, well, what I found
is I found about half a gram
of powder cocaine

